                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17240226-63-off318 t17240226-63-cd319"></join> last, who were convicted for the Fact this present Sessions. The Prosecutor depos'd. That being inform'd by one Aldersey, that the Prisoner had bought his Tallow, he got a Warrant for apprehending him, and he own'd he bought it for 8 or 9 Shillings, and had burnt the Basket, and described the Basket, so that by his Description it appeared to be his Basket, and there was in it such sort of Stuff, that any Tallow-Chandler must needs know that it was stolen. Two other Evidences depos'd, The Prisoner own'd that he bought such a Parcel of Tallow and burnt the Basket. Stephen Aldersey depos'd, He and his Accomplices sold the Tallow to the Prosecutor for 9 s. and 6 full Pots of Drink, and that he said if they would bring him any Tallow, he would let them in at any Time at his back Door. The Prisoner own'd that he bought the Tallow; but the Persons that sold him it, told him that it was honestly come by, and he gave the full Value of it. He called several to his Reputation; but the Jury being satisfied in the Evidence against him, he was found <rs id="t17240226-63-verdict320" type="verdictDescription">
